items.title: Porcupine in Wildflowers
items.description:
Dan King Alaskan Photography posted a photo:

We had to travel down to Anchorage for medical reasons and on the way home, we decided to drive into Denali National Park. During the summer months, one can only drive 14 miles into the Park and often times, it is very crowded. We arrived a little before 10pm and thankfully, most people had called it a day.
Hoping to see a predator or two, we drove on our way to 14 mile. We noticed a porcupine waddling along the wildflowers eating some greens. I pulled our truck over and walked towards where the lil porky was feeding. I stood quietly for a few minutes and the porcupine walked right towards me, stopped about 20 feet away in the flowers and began eating as if I wasn't there. Of all the photos taken, this was my favorite shot. I love the way the porcupine is framed by the green vegetation and wildflowers.
We didn't see any other animals on our drive through. We were still 3 hours from home and we had a busy day at the hospital so neither one of us were up for a hike. Oh to be young and healthy again.
